 Actually I prefer the old zones for my alts, and quite like the 'lack' of other characters there. Just go to LoIO to see what I mean - more characters, more nerds. But as was pointed out, really if EQ must continue, it must expand. EQ just isn't dynamic enough for it to have a small world.<br>
<br>
On the subject, currently working on the development of a MMORPG that someone worked out that on average it would take you eight hours of travelling to run into one other character! Of course, this assumes that character's are evenly spread out, which they won't be. There might be some places that are rarely if ever visited! AND the world is going to be dynamic as well, and the plan is that there will be no zones. But I will also say we have no intentions of increasing world size with expansions either. So all this room obviously gives us a lot to work with should be wish to make some areas 'more accessible'.<br>
